# Keep the Docker build context tiny. On the deployed box the repo root holds models/ (~22GB
# GGUF) and data/ (every job's dataroom + logs + zips); `build: .` would otherwise tar all of it
# to the daemon on every `docker compose build`, defeating the fast warm-cache rebuild and risking
# ENOSPC. The Dockerfile only COPYs server/pi/templates/web/assets, so excluding these cannot
# change the image - it only shrinks the context. (.gitignore does NOT scope the build context.)
models/
data/
out/
.hf/
nginx/certs/
.git/
.github/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.zip
node_modules/
.venv/
.env
dataroom/.index*
